I'm talking to you!

1514
01:41:08,880 --> 01:41:12,362
Get the hell out of Cincinnati!
We don't want you here, boy!

1515
01:41:13,960 --> 01:41:15,610
Nigger!

1516
01:41:15,760 --> 01:41:17,603
We don't want you here!

1517
01:41:17,800 --> 01:41:19,943
Cincinnati fans expressing their
displeasure...

1518
01:41:20,043 --> 01:41:21,939
as the Dodgers take the field.

1519
01:41:22,074 --> 01:41:24,650
Jackie Robinson at first.
"The Brat" Eddie Stanky at second.

1520
01:41:24,800 --> 01:41:26,046
Spider Jorgensen at third.

1521
01:41:26,146 --> 01:41:28,534
And the captain, Pee Wee Reese,
at short.

1522
01:41:28,680 --> 01:41:30,595
Fans, ask any man and they'll
tell you...

1523
01:41:30,753 --> 01:41:33,690
the Gillette Superspeed razor
is a honey.

1524
01:41:33,840 --> 01:41:36,127
Maybe the sweetest shaving
razor you'll ever use.

1525
01:41:36,280 --> 01:41:38,965
Look sharp, feel sharp, be sharp.

1526
01:41:39,160 --> 01:41:40,730
We don't want no niggers here!

1527
01:41:40,880 --> 01:41:43,850
They can say all they want.
We're just here to play ball.

1528
01:41:44,000 --> 01:41:45,570
Get him off the field!

1529
01:41:45,720 --> 01:41:49,486
It's just a bunch of crackpots
still fighting the Civil War.

1530
01:41:49,920 --> 01:41:51,584
Well hell, we'd have won that
son of a gun...

1531
01:41:51,724 --> 01:41:53,637
if the cornstalks would have
held out.

1532
01:41:53,772 --> 01:41:55,602
We just ran out of ammunition.

1533
01:41:56,960 --> 01:41:58,883
Better luck next time, Pee Wee.

1534
01:42:02,600 --> 01:42:04,329
Ain't gonna be a next time, Jackie.

1535
01:42:04,480 --> 01:42:06,721
Hey, Reese!
Carpetbagger!

1536
01:42:06,880 --> 01:42:08,811
All we got's right here.

1537
01:42:09,373 --> 01:42:12,305
Right now.
You know what I mean?

1538
01:42:13,520 --> 01:42:14,965
Thank you, Jackie.

1539
01:42:17,000 --> 01:42:18,729
What are you thanking me for?

1540
01:42:21,960 --> 01:42:24,361
I got family up there, from
Louisville.

1541
01:42:26,520 --> 01:42:28,170
I need them to know.

1542
01:42:29,760 --> 01:42:31,728
I need them to know who I am.

1543
01:42:39,840 --> 01:42:41,080
Hey, number 1!

1544
01:42:41,800 --> 01:42:43,848
You playing ball, or socializing?

1545
01:42:45,800 --> 01:42:46,961
Playing ball, ump.

1546
01:42:47,120 --> 01:42:49,160
Play ball!
Don't let them get to you!

1547
01:42:49,280 --> 01:42:50,770
Playing ball.

1548
01:42:51,880 --> 01:42:56,681
Maybe tomorrow we'll all wear 42.
That way they won't tell us apart.

1549
01:43:04,400 --> 01:43:06,289
Come on, Jackie!

1550
01:43:15,840 --> 01:43:17,490
Let me ask you something, Jackie.

1551
01:43:17,640 --> 01:43:20,962
How come you never shower until
everybody else is done?

1552
01:43:23,560 --> 01:43:24,686
What are you, shy?

1553
01:43:29,440 --> 01:43:31,647
I don't want to make anyone feel
uncomfortable.

1554
01:43:32,360 --> 01:43:34,840
We're a team.
On a hot streak.

1555
01:43:35,000 --> 01:43:37,480
Come on, half those wins were
on account of you.

1556
01:43:38,560 --> 01:43:40,244
You're the bravest guy I ever saw.

1557
01:43:43,880 --> 01:43:46,770
You're leading us, you're afraid
to take a shower?

1558
01:43:53,640 --> 01:43:55,768
Come on, take a shower with
me, Jackie.

1559
01:44:00,320 --> 01:44:02,243
I didn't mean it like...

1560
01:44:07,320 --> 01:44:08,906
That came out a little wrong.

1561
01:44:09,006 --> 01:44:10,859
I was not saying just take a
shower with me...

1562
01:44:10,994 --> 01:44:13,491
I was saying, why don't we all
go and take a shower.

1563
01:44:13,680 --> 01:44:14,681
Like, why...
Heh.

1564
01:44:14,840 --> 01:44:17,446
As a team, why don't we shower
together.

1565
01:44:17,640 --> 01:44:20,120
Branca?
Yeah.

1566
01:44:22,160 --> 01:44:25,323
Stop.
Yeah.

1567
01:44:26,600 --> 01:44:27,886
I'm stopping.

1568
01:44:56,040 --> 01:44:59,217
We're in the last of a four-game
series with the Cardinals...

1569
01:44:59,317 --> 01:45:01,688
and these two teams are in
a dogfight for first.

1570
01:45:01,788 --> 01:45:04,522
Top of the 11th now, all tied up
at 2.

1571
01:45:04,560 --> 01:45:07,166
For those of you just tuning
in, how did we get here?

1572
01:45:07,360 --> 01:45:08,885
Well, it's been double trouble...

1573
01:45:09,040 --> 01:45:12,283
as Robinson knocked in Stanky
with a double in the 3rd.

1574
01:45:12,440 --> 01:45:13,965
Shoot two!
Shoot two!

1575
01:45:14,160 --> 01:45:16,640
And Dixie Walker did the same
with a double in the 8th.

1576
01:45:18,520 --> 01:45:20,124
Second base!
Second base!

1577
01:45:20,280 --> 01:45:21,560
But it wasn't enough...

1578
01:45:21,600 --> 01:45:24,524
as the Cardinals tied it up with
two of their own in the 9th.

1579
01:45:24,680 --> 01:45:27,126
This game is crucial to the
Red Birds.

1580
01:45:27,280 --> 01:45:29,673
They are five games out
with the Dodgers not having...

1581
01:45:29,773 --> 01:45:32,967
relinquished first place
since June 30th.

1582
01:45:33,040 --> 01:45:34,242
They call him "Country."

1583
01:45:34,364 --> 01:45:36,313
Slaughter's hitless in four
trips.

1584
01:45:36,443 --> 01:45:38,962
"Fireman" Casey in his second
inning of relief.

1585
01:45:38,997 --> 01:45:41,924
This game is just as tight as a
new pair of shoes on a rainy day.

1586
01:45:42,080 --> 01:45:44,082
Casey goes into his windup.

1587
01:45:45,200 --> 01:45:47,624
Slaughter hits a hard ground
ball right at Reese...

1588
01:45:47,724 --> 01:45:49,366
who fires it over to Jack
at first.

1589
01:45:50,200 --> 01:45:51,406
Oh, my!

1590
01:45:51,560 --> 01:45:52,764
Robinson is down.

1591
01:45:52,932 --> 01:45:56,654
Slaughter spiked him high up
on the leg, and he is down.

1592
01:45:56,789 --> 01:45:58,133
Goddamn it, Slaughter!

1593
01:45:58,233 --> 01:45:59,619
You knew what you were doing!
You spiked my guy!

1594
01:45:59,654 --> 01:46:01,045
Get up, Jackie.

1595
01:46:01,440 --> 01:46:03,522
Get him up, boys, get him up.

1596
01:46:03,680 --> 01:46:05,444
Stay off it.
Team doc will be out.

1597
01:46:05,600 --> 01:46:07,789
Hugh, next guy up, you hit him
right in the head, alright?

1598
01:46:07,889 --> 01:46:09,199
You clean his clock.
No, no, no, no, no...

1599
01:46:09,200 --> 01:46:11,601
No, no. Get me up.
No, lay down, man. You're staying.

1600
01:46:11,800 --> 01:46:13,609
No.
Get me up!

1601
01:46:15,600 --> 01:46:17,011
Easy, kid.

1602
01:46:19,120 --> 01:46:20,645
Just get him out.

1603
01:46:22,600 --> 01:46:24,125
Just get him out.

1604
01:46:24,280 --> 01:46:25,281
Understand?

1605
01:46:27,760 --> 01:46:29,125
Game's too important.

1606
01:46:31,200 --> 01:46:32,850
Just get him out.

1607
01:46:33,720 --> 01:46:34,846
Go play ball.

1608
01:46:35,000 --> 01:46:37,367
You a tough man, Jackie.
Let's get him out.

1609
01:46:37,520 --> 01:46:40,508
Jackie, what are saying?
He spiked you on purpose?

1610
01:46:40,920 --> 01:46:42,445
You saw the play.

1611
01:46:42,600 --> 01:46:44,261
My foot was on the inside of
the bag...

1612
01:46:44,361 --> 01:46:46,217
he was out by a mile, but he
kept coming.

1613
01:46:46,252 --> 01:46:48,646
So, it was on purpose?
Slaughter said it was an accident.

1614
01:46:48,800 --> 01:46:50,325
What are you asking me for, then?

1615
01:46:50,480 --> 01:46:52,801
Are you calling Slaughter a liar?
Is he a liar?

1616
01:46:52,960 --> 01:46:55,850
Am I calling him a liar?
What are you gonna write?

1617
01:46:56,000 --> 01:46:57,346
Get out of here!
Get out!

1618
01:46:57,446 --> 01:46:59,574
Come on, Rickey, let him finish
the story!

1619
01:46:59,840 --> 01:47:01,760
Go on, let me talk to my first
baseman.

1620
01:47:01,840 --> 01:47:03,046
Is he a liar, Jackie?
Go!

1621
01:47:03,200 --> 01:47:06,010
All right, all right. Getting
stitched up, for Pete's sake.

1622
01:47:06,160 --> 01:47:08,527
Just trying to do our job,
Rickey.

1623
01:47:15,440 --> 01:47:18,011
Looks good, Babe.
Thank you, sir.

1624
01:47:18,520 --> 01:47:19,941
Sticking up for himself...

1625
01:47:20,041 --> 01:47:22,802
is something you'd expect of
any man.

1626
01:47:25,720 --> 01:47:29,042
Some find it galling in a Negro.

1627
01:47:41,040 --> 01:47:43,281
You know what I saw this morning?

1628
01:47:44,920 --> 01:47:49,050
I was passing a sandlot, little
white boy was up at bat.

1629
01:47:51,200 --> 01:47:53,043
You know what he was doing?

1630
01:47:54,760 --> 01:47:56,489
Sitting on a fastball?

1631
01:47:56,640 --> 01:47:58,244
He was pretending he was you.

1632
01:47:59,320 --> 01:48:01,368
Rubbing dirt on his hands.

1633
01:48:01,560 --> 01:48:05,963
Swinging with his arms outstretched,
like you do.

1634
01:48:06,160 --> 01:48:10,768
Little white boy pretending
he is a black man.

1635
01:48:17,080 --> 01:48:19,162
Why'd you do this, Mr. Rickey?

1636
01:48:33,080 --> 01:48:35,890
We had a victory over fascism
in Germany.

1637
01:48:36,040 --> 01:48:39,647
It's time we had a victory
over racism at home.

1638
01:48:39,800 --> 01:48:41,211
No.

1639
01:48:41,760 --> 01:48:43,171
Why?

1640
01:48:44,880 --> 01:48:46,006
Why'd you do it?

1641
01:48:49,960 --> 01:48:51,291
Come on.

1642
01:48:52,480 --> 01:48:54,164
Tell me.

1643
01:48:56,960 --> 01:48:58,610
I love this game.

1644
01:48:59,880 --> 01:49:01,769
I love baseball.

1645
01:49:03,640 --> 01:49:05,642
Given my whole life to it.

1646
01:49:08,440 --> 01:49:10,877
Forty-odd years ago, I was a
player-coach...

1647
01:49:10,977 --> 01:49:13,820
at Ohio Wesleyan University.

1648
01:49:14,120 --> 01:49:18,205
We had a Negro catcher.
Best hitter on the team.

1649
01:49:18,880 --> 01:49:21,929
Charlie Thomas.
Fine young man.

1650
01:49:22,480 --> 01:49:27,327
I saw him laid low, broken,
because of the color of his skin.

1651
01:49:27,480 --> 01:49:29,482
And I didn't do enough to help.

1652
01:49:29,640 --> 01:49:32,041
Told myself I did, but I didn't.

1653
01:49:33,160 --> 01:49:38,451
There was something unfair at
the heart of the game I loved...

1654
01:49:38,640 --> 01:49:40,005
and I ignored it.

1655
01:49:44,680 --> 01:49:46,409
But a time came...

1656
01:49:47,320 --> 01:49:49,687
when I could no longer do that.

1657
01:49:53,160 --> 01:49:54,764
You...

1658
01:49:57,280 --> 01:49:59,886
you let me love baseball again.

1659
01:50:05,560 --> 01:50:06,846
Thank you.

1660
01:50:14,320 --> 01:50:17,085
Last long road trip of the year.

1661
01:50:18,280 --> 01:50:20,726
And two long faces, huh?

1662
01:50:36,240 --> 01:50:38,288
Try not to lunge at the plate.

1663
01:50:40,200 --> 01:50:41,690
You serious?

1664
01:50:41,840 --> 01:50:44,684
That's why they're throwing
the fastballs inside.

1665
01:50:45,920 --> 01:50:48,241
Fight those inside fastballs
off...

1666
01:50:48,400 --> 01:50:52,644
sooner or later they won't be
able to help, but, throw a curve.

1667
01:50:53,880 --> 01:50:56,247
And what'll happen then, coach?

1668
01:51:03,240 --> 01:51:05,083
Is that right?
Mm-hm.

1669
01:51:06,080 --> 01:51:09,562
Well, you know, if we win enough
of these next games...

1670
01:51:10,080 --> 01:51:11,844
we bring home the pennant.

1671
01:51:13,120 --> 01:51:15,009
You bring yourself home.

1672
01:51:16,080 --> 01:51:17,730
That'll be plenty.

1673
01:51:19,000 --> 01:51:20,604
You're in my heart.

1674
01:51:23,960 --> 01:51:25,130
Since the 4th of July...

1675
01:51:25,230 --> 01:51:27,779
the Brooklyn Dodgers have gone
on a hot streak...

1676
01:51:27,914 --> 01:51:30,040
holding off all challengers.

1677
01:51:30,440 --> 01:51:32,283
During that time and during
this season...

1678
01:51:32,440 --> 01:51:35,046
I have watched Jackie Robinson
submerge himself...

1679
01:51:35,200 --> 01:51:36,850
to serve something greater.

1680
01:51:38,560 --> 01:51:39,605
And I don't mean the Brooklyn
Dodgers...

1681
01:51:39,705 --> 01:51:42,010
though he's doing that, too.

1682
01:51:42,600 --> 01:51:45,763
The man flat-out has guts.

1683
01:51:45,920 --> 01:51:46,997
A stand-up force of nature...

1684
01:51:47,097 --> 01:51:49,417
he's complicated everything
but himself.

1685
01:51:49,552 --> 01:51:52,807
He's changing the world and
refusing to let it change him.

1686
01:51:54,360 --> 01:51:56,249
But baseball isn't tennis.

1687
01:51:56,440 --> 01:51:58,169
It takes a team.

1688
01:51:59,120 --> 01:52:01,487
Joining together was a start.

1689
01:52:01,640 --> 01:52:03,802
Staying together, a big step
forward.

1690
01:52:03,960 --> 01:52:06,122
But working together is how
you win.

1691
01:52:06,320 --> 01:52:07,560
Out!

1692
01:52:09,360 --> 01:52:11,328
Jackie, you son of a gun,
I could kiss you!

1693
01:52:11,480 --> 01:52:12,641
Nice catch.

1694
01:52:12,800 --> 01:52:14,290
Yours, or mine?
Heh.

1695
01:52:14,800 --> 01:52:17,485
Down the stretch on the last
long road trip of the year...

1696
01:52:17,640 --> 01:52:21,008
Jackie Robinson and the Brooklyn
Dodgers are doing exactly that.

1697
01:52:21,800 --> 01:52:25,088
They're holding off the Cardinals
and streaking towards the pennant.

1698
01:52:27,840 --> 01:52:30,320
Boss, we did it.

1699
01:52:30,480 --> 01:52:32,721
We did it, we swept Cincinnati!

1700
01:52:32,880 --> 01:52:34,291
Great, Harold.

1701
01:52:34,440 --> 01:52:36,329
One more win could do it.

1702
01:52:36,480 --> 01:52:38,528
Who's pitching tomorrow for
the Pirates?

1703
01:52:39,680 --> 01:52:41,330
Ostermueller.

1704
01:52:44,080 --> 01:52:46,003
Fritz Ostermueller on the mound.

1705
01:52:46,160 --> 01:52:47,844
He's 12-8 on the season.

1706
01:52:48,000 --> 01:52:50,241
A big game today in Pittsburgh.

1707
01:52:50,400 --> 01:52:51,930
A win, and the Dodgers will
have clinched...

1708
01:52:52,030 --> 01:52:53,356
the National League pennant...

1709
01:52:53,456 --> 01:52:56,366
Yankees having already clinched
in the American League.

1710
01:52:56,520 --> 01:52:57,681
There's bad blood here...

1711
01:52:57,840 --> 01:53:01,526
as Ostermueller beaned Robinson
in the head earlier in the season...

1712
01:53:01,680 --> 01:53:04,251
prompting quite a rhubarb at
the time.

1713
01:53:05,960 --> 01:53:07,883
Teams have gone their separate
ways since...

1714
01:53:08,040 --> 01:53:10,520
with Ostermueller left standing
in the Dodgers' way...

1715
01:53:10,720 --> 01:53:13,291
as they chase the pennant that
eluded them last year.

1716
01:53:13,440 --> 01:53:15,249
Come on, Jackie, let's go!

1717
01:53:19,560 --> 01:53:20,760
Here comes the pitch.

1718
01:53:21,320 --> 01:53:23,368
And Robinson takes outside.
Ball one.

1719
01:53:23,560 --> 01:53:26,928
Come on, Fritz, let's get this boy!
You don't belong here.

1720
01:53:27,120 --> 01:53:28,645
And you never will.

1721
01:53:28,800 --> 01:53:30,484
Robinson crowding the plate.

1722
01:53:30,640 --> 01:53:32,927
Jack hasn't backed down to
a pitcher all season.

1723
01:53:33,080 --> 01:53:34,161
There you go, Jackie!

1724
01:53:34,320 --> 01:53:38,564
You got nothing for him, Ostermueller!
But he's got something for you!

1725
01:53:40,880 --> 01:53:42,882
Ostermueller winds and throws.

1726
01:53:43,080 --> 01:53:44,844
Low and away, ball two.

1727
01:53:45,120 --> 01:53:47,122
Fritz seems to be pitching
around Jackie...

1728
01:53:47,280 --> 01:53:50,250
or as they say in the trade,
trying to get him to chase.

1729
01:53:50,400 --> 01:53:52,402
Robinson's having a fine
rookie standard...

1730
01:53:52,560 --> 01:53:55,643
batting .301 with 31 doubles
and 10 home runs.

1731
01:53:55,800 --> 01:53:58,327
He has stolen 27 bases this
season, and has yet...

1732
01:53:58,427 --> 01:54:00,200
to be thrown out attempting.

1733
01:54:00,580 --> 01:54:03,201
Needless to say, Ostermueller
being careful with him.

1734
01:54:05,240 --> 01:54:06,969
It's 3-0, now.

1735
01:54:07,520 --> 01:54:10,444
Robinson patient, waiting for
something he can swing on.

1736
01:54:10,920 --> 01:54:12,445
Give me something.

1737
01:54:13,880 --> 01:54:15,405
Give me something I can hit.

1738
01:54:15,560 --> 01:54:16,766
You want it?

1739
01:54:16,920 --> 01:54:18,490
What are you afraid, of?

1740
01:54:28,320 --> 01:54:30,129
What are you afraid, of?

1741
01:54:32,160 --> 01:54:33,969
Ostermueller looking in for
the sign.

1742
01:54:34,120 --> 01:54:36,771
Be careful what you ask for,
boy.

1743
01:54:41,560 --> 01:54:43,449
And here comes the pitch.

1744
01:54:47,440 --> 01:54:49,602
Oh, and that's a deep fly ball
to left.

1745
01:54:49,760 --> 01:54:52,001
Kiner on his horse, I don't
think he'll get there.

1746
01:54:52,160 --> 01:54:53,730
Back, back, back, and...

1747
01:54:53,880 --> 01:54:56,360
Oh, ho, ho, doctor!

1748
01:54:56,520 --> 01:54:58,648
Robinson got his pitch!

1749
01:54:58,800 --> 01:55:00,040
It's a home run.

1750
01:55:01,440 --> 01:55:02,771
And barring a miracle comeback...

1751
01:55:02,920 --> 01:55:05,810
the Dodgers are going to the
World Series!

1752
01:55:06,000 --> 01:55:07,001
Yes!

1753
01:55:08,640 --> 01:55:10,005
He did it, he did it!

1754
01:55:21,680 --> 01:55:23,330
Pittsburgh!

1755
01:55:27,320 --> 01:55:28,367
Yes!

1756
01:55:28,680 --> 01:55:30,364
Way to go, Jackie!

1757
01:55:33,360 --> 01:55:35,083
Jack in his home run trot, now...

1758
01:55:35,183 --> 01:55:36,899
and the home crowd here at
Forbes...

1759
01:55:36,934 --> 01:55:39,486
recognizing something special
